HEADWORD: Hydrokinetic
<hw>Hy`dro*ki*net"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hydro-</ets>, 1 + <ets>kinetic</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or
pertaining to the motions of fluids, or the forces which produce or
affect such motions; -- opposed to <contr>hydrostatic</contr>.</def>
<rj><au>Sir W. Thomson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

